  "title": "Carpenter Supervisor",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Summary</strong></p><p>You will plan and organize daily site works based on the project schedule, ensure tasks are completed on time, perform carpentry works and inspections, and report defects or non-compliances to the Project Manager.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Analyze the project schedule to plan daily site activities effectively</li><li>Monitor and ensure site works follow the schedule and meet completion targets</li><li>Perform carpentry works and conduct inspections to maintain quality standards</li><li>Identify and report defects or non-compliances promptly to the Project Manager</li><li>Apply knowledge from at least 5 years of construction site experience, especially in reinforced concrete (RC) works</li><li>Utilize experience from medium to large projects, including HDB and private flats, to manage site tasks efficiently</li></ul><p><strong>Preferred competencies and qualifications</strong></p><ul><li>Minimum 10 years of working experience in construction sites, particularly for RC works</li><li>Experience working on medium to large projects for HDB and private flats</li></ul>",
